text: Sparks is a city in Washoe County, Nevada, United States. It was founded in 1904 and is just east of Reno. As of the 2020 U.S. Census, 108,445 people live in the city. It is the fifth-largest city by population in Nevada. == References == Category:1904 establishments in the United States Category:1900s establishments in Nevada Category:Cities in Nevada
title: Sparks, Nevada
